A weathered medieval stone bridge stretching across a misty chasm, with one half built from ancient crumbling bricks showing moss and age, while the other half transitions into sleek modern steel and glass construction. Studio Ghibli style with soft watercolor textures and dreamy atmospheric lighting. Tiny figures of workers can be seen on scaffolding at the junction point where old meets new, some pulling the old stones forward while others push the new materials back. Floating debris of broken code-like stone tablets drift in the fog below. The sky shows both a warm sunset on the old side and a cool dawn on the new side, creating a visual tension. Lush vegetation creeps up the ancient portion while geometric patterns adorn the modern section. Birds circle overhead, some flying toward the past, others toward the future.
